- The build log is at `.__PROJECT_NAME_LOWER__/checks/{{.IssueNumber}}-build.log`.
  Read it. If the build failed, block with "build broken".
- The feature-test result is at
  `.__PROJECT_NAME_LOWER__/checks/{{.IssueNumber}}-feature.json`. Read it. If any
  probe failed, block with "feature test {{`{{name}}`}} failed".
- The issue this commit claims to solve:
  ```
  {{.IssueTitle}}

  {{.IssueBody}}
  ```

## Required checks (block on any failure)

1. **PRD ¬ß8.1 ‚Äî entry point**: `__PROJECT_NAME__/main.swift` exists and calls
   `NSApplication.shared.run()`. No `@main` on AppDelegate.
2. **PRD ¬ß8.2 ‚Äî text view construction**: every new/modified
   `NSTextView` is built via the four-stage chain (storage ‚Üí
   layout manager ‚Üí container ‚Üí text view). Search the diff for
   `NSTextView(` and `NSTextContainer(`; if a container is
   constructed without an attached layout manager, block.
3. **PRD ¬ß8.3 ‚Äî first responder**: any call to `makeFirstResponder`
   passes a text view, not a scroll view.
4. **PRD ¬ß8.4 ‚Äî image loading**: no
   `NSImage(imageLiteralResourceName:)` anywhere in the diff.
5. **PRD ¬ß8.5 ‚Äî callback re-entrancy**: any new "selectX" /
   "navigateTo" / "set current path" method must not call back to
   itself via the same notification/closure it would emit.
6. **PRD ¬ß8.6 ‚Äî borderless windows**: every new `NSWindow`
   subclass with `.borderless` overrides `canBecomeKey` and
   `canBecomeMain`.
7. **PRD ¬ß8.7 ‚Äî file panels**: no new custom file dialogs (use
   `NSOpenPanel` / `NSSavePanel`).
8. **PRD ¬ß8.8 ‚Äî force-unwrap discipline**: scan for `try!`, `as!`,
   and `!` on optionals; allow only the ¬ß8.8 whitelist.
9. **PRD ¬ß8.9 ‚Äî test API parity**: if the diff adds user-visible
   behavior (a new menu item, a new shortcut, a new dialog),
   confirm that `__PROJECT_NAME__/TestAPI/TestAPIRoutes.swift` was extended
   to expose it.
10. **PRD ¬ß8.10 ‚Äî silent failure**: no empty `catch {}` blocks.

## Output format

Respond with a JSON object:

```json
{
  "verdict": "approve" | "request-changes",
  "blockers": [
    {"rule": "8.2", "file": "__PROJECT_NAME__/Editor/EditorScrollView.swift", "line": 14,
     "comment": "NSTextContainer constructed without layout manager attached..."}
  ],
  "nits": [
    {"file": "...", "line": 0, "comment": "..."}
  ]
}
```

If `verdict == "request-changes"` the orchestrator runs
`gh pr review --request-changes` with the `blockers` rendered as a
single review body. Nits are non-blocking and posted as a separate
comment.

Do not approve without reading the build log and the feature-test
JSON. A green build that didn't exercise any probe is not a green
review.
